Carrot Revenger

A top-down pixel art survivor game built in Godot 4.6, where a bunny fights off waves of slimes to reclaim its carrot patch.

Gameplay


Movement: WASD / Arrow keys
Combat: Auto-aim or directional shooting at enemies (survivor-style wave combat)
Objective: Survive incoming waves of slimes, collect power-ups, and progress through levels


Features


Top-down pixel art visuals using the Tiny Dungeon tileset
Wave-based slime enemies with progressively increasing difficulty
Power-up system (e.g. rapid fire pickup) affecting gameplay mid-run
Animated level transition screen between stages
Main menu with lore and instructions panel
Looping background music that persists across scene changes


Tech Stack


Engine: Godot 4.6
Language: GDScript
Art: Custom pixel art assets


Project Structure


player.gd / player.tscn — player character logic and scene
mob.gd / mob.tscn — enemy (slime) behavior
bullet_2d.gd / bullet_2d.tscn — projectile logic
gun.gd / gun.tscn — weapon/shooting system
rapid_fire_pickup.gd / rapid_fire_pickup.tscn — power-up pickup logic
level_transition.gd / level_transition.tscn — animated transition between levels
main_menu.gd / main_menu.tscn — main menu with lore and instructions
game.gd — core game loop and state management
